      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Here are a few options for a rejection email, but I've kept them suitably polished for a senior role. You want to be professional, even when the decision is tough, which is a lot like telling a very skilled but ultimately unsuited apprentice that they can't join the main guild. It's always a delicate dance, and the candidate deserves respect, even if they weren't the right fit for the current needs of the company.\n\n***\n\n**Option 1: Warm and Encouraging (Good for keeping the door open)**\n\nSubject: Update on the Senior Developer Position at [Company Name]\n\nDear [Candidate Name],\n\nThank you so much for taking the time to interview with our team for the Senior Developer position. We truly enjoyed getting to know you and learning more about your impressive background in [mention a specific skill or area]. The final round was incredibly competitive, and we were genuinely impressed by your skills; however, we have decided to move forward with another candidate whose experience was a slightly closer match to our immediate needs for this particular role.\n\nPlease know that this decision was extremely difficult, as your qualifications are top-tier. We wish you the very best in your job search and future endeavors. We",
